comments.body: I agree, and I will do that when we get to the point where we can create an invalid record. Right now, we are using the CDL datacite-mapping gem to make the records, and they literally cannot create an invalid one. They will throw an error if they try. However, as we move forward and encode our local practices into our local copy of the schema, then we will start being able to observe places where we have datacite valid records that are not valid according to our local practices.
